Assuming that your component relies on the inital state of the `optional` state being the `null` value (rather than `undefined`), one solution would be to explicitly specify the state hooks type as a [union type][1] of both `number` and `null` like so:

    // Allows initial value to be null, and number to be subsequently set 
    const [optional, setOptional] = useState&lt;number | null&gt;(null);

    // optional === null

    setOptional(42);

Alternatively, if your component does not distingush between `undefined` or `null` for the inital `optional` state value, then the following would work:

    const [optional, setOptional] = useState&lt;number&gt;();

    // optional === undefined

    setOptional(42);


  [1]: https://www.typescriptlang.org/docs/handbook/advanced-types.html#union-types

